{"info": {"author": "Emilio Escobar", "author_email": "eescobar@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": [], "description": "Slack Signature Authentication for Flask\n========================================\n.. image:: https://travis-ci.org/eaescob/flask-slacksigauth.svg?branch=master\n    :target: https://travis-ci.org/eaescob/flask-slacksigauth\n.. image:: https://codecov.io/gh/eaescob/flask-slacksigauth/branch/master/graph/badge.svg\n    :target: https://codecov.io/gh/eaescob/flask-slacksigauth\n\nThe Slack Signature Authentication module is a Python-based solution for Flask applications\nto be able to authenticate POST requests coming in from Slack. The module returns HTTP code\n403 for those requests that fail Slack's signature validation. The module adds a decorator\nthat can be used for Flask routes.\n\nInstallation\n------------\n.. code:: shell\n\n  pip install flask-slacksigauth\n\nApp Setup\n------------\nAfter declaring your Flask API endpoints, you can decorate them to for authentication checks:\n\n.. code:: python\n\n  @app.route('/api', methods=['POST', 'GET'])\n  @slack_sig_auth\n  def api():\n    return jsonify(message='OK'), 200\n\n**This will force slack signature authentication for you '/api' endoint.**\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/x-rst", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/eaescob/flask-slacksigauth", "keywords": "", "license": "GNU", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "flask-slacksigauth", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/flask-slacksigauth/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/flask-slacksigauth/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/eaescob/flask-slacksigauth"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/flask-slacksigauth/1.0.6/", "requires_dist": ["flask", "pyee", "requests", "six"], "requires_python": "", "summary": "Python Flask adapter for verifying Slack signatures", "version": "1.0.6", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <a href=\"https://travis-ci.org/eaescob/flask-slacksigauth\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"https://travis-ci.org/eaescob/flask-slacksigauth.svg?branch=master\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/23800978deb2eb1fd74dc144ceefe30a2c660933/68747470733a2f2f7472617669732d63692e6f72672f65616573636f622f666c61736b2d736c61636b736967617574682e7376673f6272616e63683d6d6173746572\"></a>\n<a href=\"https://codecov.io/gh/eaescob/flask-slacksigauth\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"https://codecov.io/gh/eaescob/flask-slacksigauth/branch/master/graph/badge.svg\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/827492c57ae9823f7df2631c51cc39f227804697/68747470733a2f2f636f6465636f762e696f2f67682f65616573636f622f666c61736b2d736c61636b736967617574682f6272616e63682f6d61737465722f67726170682f62616467652e737667\"></a>\n<p>The Slack Signature Authentication module is a Python-based solution for Flask applications\nto be able to authenticate POST requests coming in from Slack. The module returns HTTP code\n403 for those requests that fail Slack\u2019s signature validation. The module adds a decorator\nthat can be used for Flask routes.</p>\n<div id=\"installation\">\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<pre>pip install flask-slacksigauth\n</pre>\n</div>\n<div id=\"app-setup\">\n<h2>App Setup</h2>\n<p>After declaring your Flask API endpoints, you can decorate them to for authentication checks:</p>\n<pre><span class=\"nd\">@app</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">route</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'/api'</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">methods</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"s1\">'POST'</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s1\">'GET'</span><span class=\"p\">])</span>\n<span class=\"nd\">@slack_sig_auth</span>\n<span class=\"k\">def</span> <span class=\"nf\">api</span><span class=\"p\">():</span>\n  <span class=\"k\">return</span> <span class=\"n\">jsonify</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">message</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"s1\">'OK'</span><span class=\"p\">),</span> <span class=\"mi\">200</span>\n</pre>\n<p><strong>This will force slack signature authentication for you \u2018/api\u2019 endoint.</strong></p>\n</div>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 7007549, "releases": {"1.0.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "ef7fe768fea416575e9258e723765a63", "sha256": "b6c8f52532f429dc10dd0da69ee0d5f80ebcdc876146eff0a5874db18ea8fa3b"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "flask_slacksigauth-1.0.0-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "ef7fe768fea416575e9258e723765a63", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": null, "size": 14424, "upload_time": "2020-04-13T00:32:11", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-04-13T00:32:11.170507Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/f1/66/ea8a196523bf5d553c9d8dbff4a6cb1c2f3f5be67c6ca14dfacc109c121a/flask_slacksigauth-1.0.0-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "ad6c2fca0cc684769d677fa70abc392c", "sha256": "f410e41acec6eb925cbeb7d7c2459f45fc2fc945ea6011b88b6cf6d99ecc965b"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "flask_slacksigauth-1.0.0.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "ad6c2fca0cc684769d677fa70abc392c", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 1689, "upload_time": "2020-04-13T00:32:13", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-04-13T00:32:13.000866Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/81/be/084a12e46ef545fa7d83bae6f6d60d309333fd3f1aa5714e09a27bcfec8f/flask_slacksigauth-1.0.0.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "1.0.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "9e39966189d44bde5bc49e69dcfb912c", "sha256": "02ebbee39855205daab30cb2f4839d19118f69c76100658a0a87512b1bcc12ec"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "flask_slacksigauth-1.0.1-py3-none-any.whl", "h